AWS AI Assistant – End-to-End Implementation

🧠 1. Created Amazon Bedrock Agent
Agent Name: CloudFolks-AWS-Admin-Agent
Model: Nova Pro
Purpose: Automate AWS resource discovery and cost optimization


🧾 2. Defined Agent Instructions

Designed safe workflow:

Discover → Explain → Recommend → Confirm → Delete
Prevented direct deletion without confirmation


🔐 3. Created IAM Role #1 (Tool Lambda Role)
Role Name: BedrockCostAgentLambdaRole
Permissions:
EC2 (Describe, Release Elastic IP)
EBS (Describe, Delete Snapshots)
CloudWatch Logs


⚙️ 4. Created Lambda Function #1
Function Name: BedrockCostAgentTools
Purpose:
Identify chargeable resources
Perform deletion operations


🔧 5. Implemented Lambda Logic
discover_cost_resources → scans AWS resources
delete_cost_resource → deletes resource after confirmation


🔗 6. Created Action Group
Name: CostCleanupTools
Connected Lambda: BedrockCostAgentTools


🧩 7. Exposed Functions to Agent
Resource discovery function
Resource deletion function (with CONFIRM token)


🧪 8. Tested Agent in Bedrock Console
Tested scenarios:
Discover resources
Delete Elastic IP
Verified confirmation workflow


🔐 9. Created IAM Role #2 (Chat Proxy Role)
Role Name: BedrockAgentChatProxyRole
Permissions:
bedrock:InvokeAgent
CloudWatch Logs


⚙️ 10. Created Lambda Function #2
Function Name: BedrockAgentChatProxy
Purpose:
Connect frontend with Bedrock Agent


🧠 11. Implemented Chat Proxy Logic
Accepts user input
Invokes Bedrock Agent
Returns formatted response


🔑 12. Added Environment Variables
AGENT_ID → Bedrock Agent ID
AGENT_ALIAS_ID → Agent Alias ID


🔄 13. Created Bedrock Agent Alias
Alias Name: production
Associated with latest agent version
Generated Alias ID


🌐 14. Created API Gateway
API Name: Chat-Integration
Type: HTTP API


🔗 15. Configured Route
POST /chat


🔌 16. Attached Lambda Integration
Integrated with: BedrockAgentChatProxy


🌍 17. Enabled CORS
Allow-Origin: *
Methods: POST, OPTIONS
Headers: *


🚀 18. Deployed API
Generated endpoint:
https://<api-id>.execute-api.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/chat


💻 19. Setup Frontend using S3
Bucket Name: ritik-bedrock-agent-chat-ui
Enabled static website hosting
Uploaded index.html
Updated API URL in frontend code


🔓 20. Enabled Public Access
Added bucket policy to allow public read access
Hosted chatbot UI accessible via S3 website endpoint


🎯 Final Outcome
Built an AI-powered AWS assistant that:
Detects chargeable resources
Explains cost impact
Performs safe deletion after confirmation
